@author:
Good questions !

For question 1: There can be a weeks between the time a dataset in added on master and the time a new version of `datasets` is released. This fallback on the `master` branch makes it possible for anyone to load a dataset that was just added on `master` without waiting for a release or installing from source. In particular, the https://hf.co/datasets page is synced with the `master` branch, therefore user expect to be able to load any dataset from the website, and this features enables this.

For question 2: you're right, we shouldn't try again if the user specified a `revision` (that could be master or any other revision). Thanks for catching this !

